The paper discusses the use of Recurrent Neural Networks (RNN) for time series forecasting, which is a topic that falls under the machine learning and artificial intelligence subfields of computer science. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, RNNs are a type of neural network, which falls under the subfield of neural networks and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the comparison of RNNs with established statistical models, which falls under the subfield of statistics (cs.ST). Finally, the paper presents guidelines and best practices for the use of RNNs in time series forecasting, which could be considered as a subfield of data mining and information retrieval (cs.SI).
